Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop the @king prawns{150%g} and the lime zest in a #bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then set to one side.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} to the boiling water and cook for ~{12%mins}. Drain in a #sieve{} then return to the saucepan and set aside. Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @black beans{1/2%can} in a sieve.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add the garlic, @Caribbean Style Jerk{1} spice mix and @tomato puree{15%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until fragrant, ~{2%mins}. Pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @KNORR Vegetable Stock{1} pot and @water for the curry{100%ml}. Stir to dissolve stock, add the black beans and bring to a simmer. Add a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir the prawns into the sauce. Cook until the prawns are cooked, ~{5%mins}, stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle!

Once the prawns are almost cooked, add the @baby spinach{125%g} to the curry, a handful at a time, stirring until it has wilted in to the sauce. Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, squeeze half the lime juice.

Once the spinach has wilted, season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide the rice between your bowls with the prawn and black bean curry spooned on top. Serve with the remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!